# Phase 9 — Live-fire graduation soak (example crontab fragment)
#
# 1. Replace /ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/JARVIS-AI-Agent with your clone.
# 2. crontab -e and paste ONE line (uncommented), or use:
#      bash scripts/install_live_fire_soak_cron.sh --install
#
# Schedule: every 8 hours (~3 soaks/day). Tunes via COST_CAP / WALL / TIMEOUT.
#
# Env block (must match parent harness needs + PRD P9.2 + Option C):
#   JARVIS_GRADUATION_LEDGER_ENABLED — parent process ledger writes after soak
#   JARVIS_LIVE_FIRE_GRADUATION_SOAK_ENABLED — allow forked battle test
#   JARVIS_LIVE_FIRE_USE_GRADUATION_CONTRACT — block false CLEAN (0-op, etc.)
#   JARVIS_DW_TOPOLOGY_EARLY_REJECT_ENABLED — clean DW-topology reject path
#   JARVIS_PHASE9_ORCHESTRATOR_ENABLED — §3.6.2 vector #6 producer-loop
#       wiring (2026-05-07): populates .jarvis/graduation_interaction_matrix
#       .jsonl so /phase9 partners surfaces co-soak data as cadence runs.
#       Operator-binding decision — explicit cadence-host opt-in (no silent
#       no-op in production).
#   OUROBOROS_BATTLE_SEED_INTENTS=3 — Phase 9 Slice 3 synthetic workload
#       injection so headless cadence soaks actually exercise the FSM
#       (closes ops_count=0 → P9.2 contract downgrade-to-RUNNER blocker).
#       Routes through canonical UnifiedIntakeRouter; envelopes carry
#       source="cadence_synthetic" so observability never confuses test
#       load with real signal traffic.
#
# Log directory is created by install_live_fire_soak_cron.sh; for a manual
# one-liner, mkdir -p the log dir first.

# LOG_DIR=/ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/JARVIS-AI-Agent/.jarvis/live_fire_soak_logs
# 0 */8 * * * cd /ABSOLUTE/PATH/TO/JARVIS-AI-Agent && JARVIS_GRADUATION_LEDGER_ENABLED=true JARVIS_LIVE_FIRE_GRADUATION_SOAK_ENABLED=true JARVIS_LIVE_FIRE_USE_GRADUATION_CONTRACT=true JARVIS_DW_TOPOLOGY_EARLY_REJECT_ENABLED=true JARVIS_PHASE9_ORCHESTRATOR_ENABLED=true OUROBOROS_BATTLE_SEED_INTENTS=3 /usr/bin/env python3 scripts/live_fire_graduation_soak.py run --cost-cap 0.50 --max-wall-seconds 2400 --timeout 3600 >> .jarvis/live_fire_soak_logs/cron.log 2>&1
